With many studio albums, films, media appearances and awards under his belt this is one entertainment powerhouse not to be missed., 3664=As it turned out, rock was a saving grace for this rapper, and it was an appearance at Lollapalooza in 1997 that put the wheels in motion for Snoop to be labeled a cultural phenomenon. First came the album "Da Game Is to Be Sold Not to Be Told. A year later he released "No Limit Top Dogg," and "The Last Meal" the year after that. All of them showed the new Snoop – the one of varying musical styles, but known as much for his personality as he was for his music., 3156=The turn of the century saw Snoop release an autobiography, and he landed several movie roles that kept his name in the mainstream consciousness. Of course there were more albums – five in seven years to be exact (2002-2009) and he capitalized on business opportunities left and right, landing at the reactivated Priority label as its creative chairman. In 2011, he released "Doggumentary," an album he touted as the sequel to his debut. It was followed in 2013 by "Reincarnated," and in June 2013 producer Symbolyc One (S1) announced Snoop was working on his final album under the moniker Snoop Dog.}
